
    A journalist at a media company in Cape Town and a resident
from Mitchells Plain have been arrested for allegedly committing fraud to allow
a parolee to move around and commit crime.Western Cape police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana
on Friday said the media company employee, a 40-year-old woman from Parow, as
well as the man from Portlands, Mitchells Plain, were arrested on Thursday.The man was taken into custody at a business premises in
